description: UI lane routing for client work (design, accessibility, motion, perf)
globs: client/src/**/*.ts*
alwaysApply: false
---

# UI lane (client)

- For page/component design or visual polish: use frontend-design (or interface-design for app-like surfaces). Use design-lab when multiple directions are useful.
- For microinteractions, transitions, loading/empty states: use interaction-design.
- For accessibility: use fixing-accessibility; for audits: wcag-audit-patterns; for general UX/UI best practices: web-design-guidelines.
- For animation quality: use 12-principles-of-animation; for jank/perf: fixing-motion-performance; for React perf: vercel-react-best-practices.
- For metadata/OG/title issues: use fixing-metadata.
